# How to start server?
node server.js 

# What's the contract?

* POST /api/temperature [{"value": 22}] - returns latest record of temperature

[QUOTE]
GET /api/temperature HTTP/1.1
Host: localhost:8080
Content-Type: application/json
Cache-Control: no-cache
Salt: 1235
Hash: 1e1a642f16892ef7ca87b2307adafc09
[/QUOTE]


* POST /api/temperature/{number} [{value: 23, timestamp: 2132132132}]  - return record of given number (counting backwards)

[QUOTE]
GET /api/temperature HTTP/1.1
Host: localhost:8080
Content-Type: application/json
Cache-Control: no-cache
Salt: 1235
Hash: 1e1a642f16892ef7ca87b2307adafc09
[/QUOTE]

# How to calculate hash?

MD5(CRYPTO_KEY + SALT + CRYPTO_KEY);

Salt should be different every time.